title: Linda

---

Linda: — W-why am in the car? I was just crossing the street, when everything went black. Now I'm here...

Charon: — You haven't recalled it yet. This is normal, considering the circumstances. There's no need to be nervous. 

Linda: —  That black car barreling at me... it really was there... I really saw it...

Charon: — I do not wish to upset you even more, but you really have died.

Linda: — No, no, no! This couldn't happen! It cannot be! My fellow nurses at the hospital... I promised them I would take an extra shift today. We got several little ones yesterday, they need thorough care, but the hospital is understaffed. The nurses are almost collapsing from exhaustion... 

Linda: — And Mrs Rodgers...  I told her I would visit her next week. No-one knows who I would become if not for her. I wanted so much to thank her again for everything she had done for me...

Linda: — And my dear Uncle John... He has a heart condition. If he hears I'm dead... please, please, let him be all right! I was just about to adopt a kitten for both of us. Uncle John would have a great companion for the day, and I would see the fluffy little ball of joy in the evening. And now... Uncle John will be alone again... 

Charon: — Linda, please, listen…  

Linda: — I just finished my education and began my career. I had a whole bunch of plans. I even thought I...

Charon: — I wanted to tell you… 

Linda: — Oh no... Martin! I know he's strong, he'll be fine, of course, he'll be fine… but I've never told him… 

Linda: — No! I couldn't die! I couldn't up and disappear! This is even worse than betrayal, I simply vanished... I vanished from their lives and left nothing to lean on... nothing at all…

Charon: — Linda! Please, believe me! You didn't vanish! Your existence is not over. Look out of the window. We have arrived. 

Linda: …

Charon: …

Linda: — Such a strange place. It doesn't look much like paradise... and yet it looks so much like it.

Charon: — We are across the bridge. I believe that here you will find everything you're looking for.

Linda: — Do you really mean it?

Charon: — Yes.

Linda: — I… believe you. Thank you for the ride.

Charon: — You're welcome, Linda.

